# Monorepo Layout Rules

## Intent
Define the required repository structure for the rewrite monorepo under `ctf/`.

## Required Root Shape
- `ctf/package.json`
- `ctf/pnpm-workspace.yaml`
- `ctf/tsconfig.base.json`
- `ctf/packages/shared`
- `ctf/packages/web`
- `ctf/packages/mobile`
- `ctf/scripts`

## Workspace Rules
- Use `pnpm` as the default package manager for deterministic workspace installs.
- Use TypeScript project references so shared types are consumed without ad-hoc duplication.
- Keep all cross-package imports through package entry points, not deep relative paths.
- Preserve clear ownership boundaries: each package has explicit maintainers and README contract.

## Script Contract
- Root scripts must include `lint`, `typecheck`, `test`, `build` orchestrating workspace packages.
- `scripts/` contains operational helpers only; business logic remains inside packages.

## Prohibited
- Creating app code outside `ctf/packages/*`.
- Mixing platform-specific code into root scripts.